$ Azure Data Lake Analytics

*Distributed analytics service that makes → development/Big-Data[big data] easy*

{ U-SQL #az-u-sql

  *U-SQL* is the big data query language for Data Lake Analytics .

  U-SQL combines
    • → development/databases/SQL[SQL's] declarative language with the
    • programmability and type system of → development/languages/C-Sharp[C#]
    • → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL

  In order to efficiently query data at a massive scale, U-SQL is optimized for parallel processing.

  U-SQL allows to query data from various sources, such as
    • → Microsoft/Azure/products/Data-Lake-Storage
    • → Microsoft/Azure/products/Blob-Storage
    • Azure SQL Data Warehouse (→ Microsoft/Azure/products/Synapse-Analytics?)
    • → development/databases/SQL-Server[SQL Server] instances running in Azure VMs.

  It should be noted that U-SQL is not → misc/ISO/9075[ANSI SQL].

}
sa:

  *Resource Providers* Data Lake Analytics include(?)
    • Microsoft.DataLakeAnalytics
  See also → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/az/ResourceProvider/get[`get-azResourceProvider`]

